  "local_port": 34792,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are the best recipes for small batch chocolate chip cookies?",
  "response": "Here are a few great recipes for small batch chocolate chip cookies that yield about 6-12 cookies, perfect for satisfying a craving without making too many!\n\n### Classic Small Batch Chocolate Chip Cookies\n\n**Ingredients:**\n- 4 tablespoons unsalted butter, melted\n- 3 tablespoons granulated sugar\n- 3 tablespoons brown sugar, packed\n- 1/4 teaspoon vanilla extract\n- Pinch of salt\n- 1/2 cup all-purpose flour\n- 1/4 teaspoon baking soda\n- 1/4 cup chocolate chips (semi-sweet or your preference)\n\n**Instructions:**\n1. Preheat your oven to 350\u00b0F (175\u00b0C) and line a baking sheet with parchment paper.\n2. In a mixing bowl, combine the melted butter, granulated sugar, brown sugar, vanilla extract, and salt. Stir until smooth.\n3. Mix in the flour and baking soda until just combined.\n4. Fold in the chocolate chips until evenly distributed.\n5. Scoop tablespoon-sized amounts of dough onto the prepared baking sheet, spaced about 2 inches apart.\n6. Bake for 8-10 minutes, or until the edges are lightly golden.\n7. Remove from the oven and allow to cool for a few minutes before transferring to a wire rack.\n\n### Brown Butter Chocolate Chip Cookies\n\n**Ingredients:**\n- 4 tablespoons unsalted butter\n- 2 tablespoons granulated sugar\n- 2 tablespoons brown sugar, packed\n- 1/4 teaspoon vanilla extract\n- Pinch of salt\n- 1/2 cup all-purpose flour\n- 1/4 teaspoon baking soda\n- 1/4 cup chocolate chips\n\n**Instructions:**\n1. In a small saucepan, melt the butter over medium heat. Continue to cook, stirring frequently, until it becomes golden brown and has a nutty aroma (about 5-7 minutes). Remove from heat and let cool slightly.\n2. Preheat your oven to 350\u00b0F (175\u00b0C) and line a baking sheet with parchment paper.\n3. In a bowl, combine the brown butter, granulated sugar, brown sugar, vanilla extract, and salt. Stir until combined.\n4. Add in the flour and baking soda, mixing until just combined.\n5. Fold in the chocolate chips.\n6. Scoop tablespoon-sized amounts of dough onto the prepared baking sheet, spacing them apart.\n7. Bake for about 8-10 minutes, or until lightly golden around the edges.\n8. Let cool for a few minutes before enjoying.\n\n### Vegan Small Batch Chocolate Chip Cookies\n\n**Ingredients:**\n- 3 tablespoons coconut oil or vegan butter, melted\n- 2 tablespoons brown sugar, packed\n- 1 tablespoon granulated sugar\n- 1/4 teaspoon vanilla extract\n- Pinch of salt\n- 1/2 cup all-purpose flour\n- 1/4 teaspoon baking soda\n- 2 tablespoons non-dairy chocolate chips\n\n**Instructions:**\n1. Preheat your oven to 350\u00b0F (175\u00b0C) and line a baking sheet with parchment paper.\n2. In a bowl, mix the melted coconut oil, brown sugar, granulated sugar, vanilla extract, and salt until well combined.\n3. Add the flour and baking soda, mixing until just incorporated.\n4. Fold in the non-dairy chocolate chips.\n5. Form tablespoon-sized balls of dough and place them on the prepared baking sheet.\n6. Bake for about 8-10 minutes, or until edges are golden.\n7. Allow cooling for a few minutes before transferring them to a wire rack.\n\n### Tips for Small Batch Cookies:\n- **Storage:** Store any leftover cookies in an airtight container at room temperature for up to a week.\n- **Customization:** You can add nuts, oats, or dried fruits to any of these recipes for added texture and flavor.\n- **Chilling the Dough:** If you have time, chill the dough for 30 minutes before baking for thicker cookies. \n\nTry out these recipes and enjoy your delicious small batch chocolate chip cookies!",
